Some constructive criticism -

Your stuff is good, your characters are interesting, and it all feels as real as a story like this can be; I'm seriously amazed as to how consistently you pump shit out, regardless of what it is, and I'm a little envious of your endurance to be honest.

Ass-kissing out of the way, SSSSS (Fuck you I'm not typing that out) could be written a little tighter. That's very fair. I think I'm too intoxicated with character writing. I love having them interact and prodding them with different stimuli. I need to try something original for once to find my own balance of pace and plot and characterization, but I've largely hated anything I work on on my own. I need that constant feedback telling me if what I'm doing is working, so having someone invested in a prompt or commission I'm doing for them is definitely a huge boost. I highly suggest anyone who has a friend willing to be a beta reader to take them up on that offer. That's not to imply that's the only thing that helps. It makes me very happy that people talk about HATSSSSS and that it has a readerbase despite its immense size along with all the fanart it's gotten.
